channel.description:
Ok, this is how to make a basic ranking system for your 317 private server.
What it does it adds a rank system which basically is a Call Of Duty style ranking. You get ranks like Private, Corperal, General, Lieutenant, etc. Also, you will be able to get killstreaks that give bonuses to the gain of your exp to rank up. Also, please don't flame, this is my first tutorial. And my second post on this forum. And I have to mention, it doesn't save for me, but I'm sure I done it before lol. And it should work with most sources, I have only used the horrible CZAR and winterLove/Blakescape D Boosted. If anyone can help me to save this, then please do. I have added the save things to PlayerHandler.java and Client.java but I really dont see why it doesnt save. Anyway, back to the TuT.

What it does: Adds a ranking system to the server.
Difficulty: 2/10
Assumed Knowledge: How to Copy+Paste.
Reason: Adds a bit more fun to PKing.
Files Modified: Client.java, PlayerHandler.java

Ok,here goes. The FIRST thing you must do is underneath
[CODE] public class client extends Player implements Runnable { [/CODE]

add these ints to the top of your Client.java
[CODE]
         // Ranking System Made by Rapidrocket7
	public int killedperson = 0;
	public int PKPointsGain = 0; // This determines how muck PKPoints will be
									// added to your characer. Will be explained
