Now to add the method to check fro killstreaks. Yet again, all explained within the code. Lets say all of it is explained within the code.

[CODE]
        // Ranking System Made by Rapidrocket7
	public void checkStreak() { // This checks if you have a new killstreak Feel
								// free to add more streaks.

		if (Streak == 3) { // If your killstreak reaches 3, it does what's
							// underneath.
			XPGain = 20; // Increases the XPGain, you will see what XPGain does
							// later. Feel free to change these.
			PKPointsGain = 2; // Also with PKPointsGain. Feel free to change
								// these.
			checkXPBooster(); // This checks if you have the XPBooster
								// (remember?)
			sendMessage("You have a 3 Kill Streak!"); // Tells you that you have
														// a 3 Kill streak.
		}
		if (Streak == 5) {
			XPGain = 30;
			PKPointsGain = 4;
			checkXPBooster();
			sendMessage("You have a 5 Kill Streak!");
		}
		if (Streak == 10) {
			XPGain = 40;
			PKPointsGain = 5;
			checkXPBooster();
			sendMessage("You have a 10 Kill Streak!");
		}
		if (Streak == 15) {
			XPGain = 50;
			PKPointsGain = 6;
			checkXPBooster();
			sendMessage("You have a 15 Kill Streak!");
		}
		if (Streak == 20) {
			XPGain = 60;
			PKPointsGain = 7;
			checkXPBooster();
			sendMessage("You have a 20 Kill Streak!");
		}
		if (Streak == 30) {
			XPGain = 70;
			PKPointsGain = 8;
			checkXPBooster();
			sendMessage("You have a 30 Kill Streak!");
		}
		if (Streak == 50) {
			XPGain = 100;
			PKPointsGain = 10;
			checkXPBooster();
			addItem(1048, 1); // Gives you a PHat, feel free to change this and
								// add it to other streaks as well as adding
								// more streaks.
			sendMessage("You have a 50 Kill Streak! Fucking Legendary! @~@~@~@");
		}
	} [/CODE]

Ok, now for the slightly trickier part, calling these when you die. Add this:
[CODE]  client killa = (client) server.playerHandler.players[KillerId]; [/CODE]
Below:
[CODE] 	public boolean ApplyDead() {[/CODE]
Ok, what that does is it shortens down "server.playerHandler.players[KillerId]" to "killa". This is very helpful and also prevents a few errors. You can change "killa" to whatever suits you, but you need to change it in the next part too.

Ok, so add this:

[CODE]
  							// Ranking System Made by Rapidrocket7
  							Streak = 0; // Resets you killstreak
				killa.PKPoints += PKPointsGain; // Adds the points to your
												// killer's PKPoints
				killa.Experience += XPGain; // Same as above, but with the
											// eperience
				killa.Streak += streakAmount; // I'm sure you get the point by
												// here.
				killa.checkRank(); // Updates your killer's rank before it
									// checks the exp.
				killa.checkExperience(); // Updates your killer's exp/rank.
				killa.checkRank(); // Re-updates your killer's callsing/prefix
				killa.checkStreak(); // Update's your killer's killstreak.
				killa.bestStreak(); // Checks if you have a new best killstreak.
				killa.sendMessage("You killed [" + Rank + "] " + playerName
						+ "."); // Tells your killer who they killed (you), Also
								// your killer him your rank
				sendMessage("You were killed by [" + Rank + "] "
						+ killa.playerName + "!"); // Tells you who killed you.
													// Also tells you your
													// killer's rank
				deathcount += 1; // Adds one death to your deathcount.
				deathstoday += 1; // you can guess. [/CODE]

